							<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
						</header>
						<p>The Summer Institute for the Gifted (SIG) and its divisions respects the privacy of visitors to our website. You control what personal information, if any, you share with us. You are not required to tell us who you are or reveal any information about yourself. This statement demonstrates our firm commitment to privacy. It discloses information-gathering and dissemination practices for the website www.giftedstudy.org.
                        </p>
						<p>The <strong>Summer Institute for the Gifted</strong> complies with the U.S.-EU Safe Harbor Framework as set forth by the U.S. Department of Commerce regarding the collection, use, and retention of personal information from European Union member countries.  The company has certified that it adheres to the Safe Harbor Privacy Principles of notice, choice, onward transfer, security, data integrity, access, and enforcement.  To learn more about the Safe Harbor program, and to view the company’s certification, please visit <a href="http://www.export.gov/safeharbor/">http://www.export.gov/safeharbor/</a>.</p>
						<p>Our web server collects your domain name but not your e-mail address. We collect the e-mail addresses of those who communicate with us via e-mail. SIG does not assemble such personal information for sale nor does SIG make addresses of our site users available to other organizations.						  </p>
						<p>We use your IP address to measure use of our site's content, help diagnose problems with our server and administer our website. Our web server automatically recognizes only the IP address, manufacturer of the web browser in use, time of use, specific files requested and referring URL. Other aggregate information is gathered from surveys or applications in which you voluntarily provide other personal data.						  </p>
						<p>Forms you fill out to interact with our business units to request literature, place an order, track an order or otherwise correspond with SIG may request personal information. For example, our site uses order forms for customers to request information, products and services. Contact information from these forms is used to send information requested.						  </p>
						<p>If you supply SIG with your e-mail or postal address, you may receive mailings with information about new products and services or upcoming events. If you do not wish to receive such mailings, notify sig.info@giftedstudy.org. The same opt-out procedure exists for phone contact from SIG. At any time you may opt out, change or modify any information provided to AIFS. By contacting <a href="mailto:sig.info@giftedstudy.org">sig.info@giftedstudy.org</a> or the appropriate division, you may remove your information from our database so as not to receive future communications.						  </p>
						<p>Our site gives users the option to change and modify information previously provided by relaying changes or modifications to SIG by calling (866) 303-4744.						  </p>
						<p>Online applications may ask for contact information such as name, e-mail address, mailing address and phone number; personal identifiers such as Social Security or passport numbers; financial information such as credit card numbers; and demographic information such as ZIP code, age, schooling or marital status. Required fields are indicated, and acceptance to a program depends on this information.						  </p>
						<p>Thwarte certifying authority, a global provider of digital certificate products, services and solutions that create security, privacy and authentication in electronic commerce, attests that the server to which any such confidential information is sent is that of SIG. Thwarte recently was acquired by VeriSign, Inc., the leading provider of internet trust services. All information—personal and financial—is handled by the SIG/AIFS secure server.						  </p>
						<p>Financial information collected is used to bill the user for products and services. Credit card information is handled by the SIG/AIFS secure server. This site has security measures in place to protect the loss, misuse and alteration of the information under our control at its Stamford, CT, headquarters, where the secure server for transactions resides.						  </p>
						<p>The SIG site contains links to non-SIG sites. Although we try to link only to website that share our respect for customer information privacy, SIG is not responsible for their privacy practices or content. SIG occasionally refers users to commercial sites where related information, services or products are available. Information supplied to these sites is at user discretion.						  </p>
						<p>Information contained in this site may also be routed through AIFS division-specific references (Au Pair in America, Summer Institute for the Gifted, Camp America, the AIFS College Division, Cultural Insurance Services International, AIFS Partnerships and Resort America). The same privacy practices are observed on any and all AIFS divisional routings bringing users to this site. AIFS divisions may share selected contact information.						  </p>
						<p>This policy may be revised over time as new features are added to the website. We will post those changes prominently so that you will always know what information we gather, how we might use that information, and whether we will disclose it to anyone. Please check this site for information about revisions to our privacy policy.						  </p>
